Prebon stared down at Slayer, his eyes flared with anger, &quot;A draw is not
good enough. Your opponent was nowhere to be scanned, that meant that it
survived while you went into stasis lock.&quot; He raised his hand as if to
strike the wolf but held back. &quot;In my opinion that qualifies as a loss, and
I don&#39;t like losers under my command.&quot;

By now ignatious and Blaze had gathered around the door listening to the
chewing out that Slayer was getting. &quot;The boss is in rare sorts today&quot;
Ignatious says, fluffing a tuft of feathers on his wrists.

&quot;First Bullet, now Slayer, we better watch our step or we&#39;re next.&quot;Blaze
replied, as she leaned closer to get a better listen.

Prebon wanted  positive results from his group, not excuses or draws.
&quot;Consider yourself lucky Slayer. I am a forgiving leader as long as I get
the results I desire, you understand don&#39;t you?&quot; He turned and started out
the door, looking over his shoulder one last time before leaving, &quot;Rest well
my servant, tomorrow we go after a bigger target than the Ark.&quot;

Blaze and Ignatious seperated and rushed around a corner before Prebon could
catch them easedropping. Both thinking &quot;Whew that was close.&quot;
